programme.desc: When an aggressive spirit stalks a young family, PRS is called in to investigate. When it is determined that the source of the haunting may have been unknowingly invited in, Ryan races to identify and hopefully defeat the entity before it's too late.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Basement
programme.desc: A history of violence may connect the spiritual activity in Heidi's Ohio home to a long run of misery and cruelty.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Cemetery
programme.desc: PRS visits a gothic graveyard, where a jealous spirit seems to be preying on the newlywed wife of the cemetery's caretaker. Ryan traces the haunting to a mysterious, unclaimed cremation urn on the grounds.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Aberglasney House
programme.desc: Multiple deaths, a curse and many hauntings draw the "Most Haunted" team to the bizarre Aberglasney House in Wales.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Schooner Hotel
programme.desc: The team investigates the Schooner Inn, a 17th-century hotel with a history of murders, suicides and massacres; babies have been reportedly thrown into fires, and sixty ghosts are said to reside there.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Fitz Manor
programme.desc: Ghostly apparitions, poltergeists and secret tunnels await the "Most Haunted" team as they visit Fitz Manor, located in the heart of rural Shropshire and overlooking the River Severn.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Muckleburgh
programme.desc: The Muckleburgh Collection is said to be haunted by the museum founder and six women of the Auxiliary Territorial Service killed on that site when an anti-aircraft gun exploded. The team investigates.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Galleries of Justice
programme.desc: Galleries of Justice is the only place in Britain where you could be arrested, sentenced and executed all in one place. With so much death and misery, the team had to explore the building.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tamworth Castle
programme.desc: Tamworth Castle is allegedly haunted by, among others, an particularly malicious spirit. Derek picks up on many spirits, including a Spanish executioner whose sword hangs in the great hall.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Owlpen Manor
programme.desc: Owlpen Manor is allegedly home to several ghosts. Queen Margaret of Anjou, wife to Henry VI, an alchemist and a young girl are all said to roam the 16th-century manor. The team investigates.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Craig-Y-Nos
programme.desc: This derelict castle in the heart of Wales has been home to a famous opera singer and a World War II hospital. This beautiful building is so haunted that the team has to spend the night.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Keep Smiling
programme.desc: Jonathan must help his own widow regain her love for life.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Last Assignment
programme.desc: An errant angel has been on probation for two centuries because he's always breaking the rules.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Bind the Wounds
programme.desc: A father attempts to have a memorial made to commemorate his son who was killed in Vietnam.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Heaven on Earth
programme.desc: Mark asks Jonathan to help erase everything bad that's happened to him recently. Mark's idea is to create his own vision of heaven on Earth.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Summit
programme.desc: A dying woman was forced to leave a son behind in the Soviet Union during World War II.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Torch
programme.desc: Tragedy occurs when a Neo-Nazi disputes the Holocaust with the son of a death camp survivor.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Sail Away
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark assist a novelist who's given up. Also, they motivate the man's grandson, who has yet to tap into his literary potential.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Children's Children
programme.desc: A reporter uncovers a secret about the past of a woman who runs a home for unwed mothers.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Chamberlain
programme.desc: For the past 12 years Sue Chamberlain has been harbouring a devastating secret. She's entirely lost her confidence and her youth. Presenter Nicky Hambleton-Jones and a team of experts revive Sue's confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Chamberlain "One Year On"
programme.desc: Just a year ago, Sue Chamberlain was a 34 year old living in a 40 year old's body. Now, a year on, we retrace Sue's transformational journey – and pop in to pay Sue a return visit. Will she still be looking fabulous – or flabby?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Tomkins
programme.desc: Night shift worker Sue Tomkins has lost her sparkle. Lank hair, haggard wrinkles, sunken eyes and weary clothes are just the starting point for Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team of experts who've got 10 days to knock 10 years off Sue's lifeless look.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand
programme.desc: Everyone wants to look younger but if you work hard and play hard like Sue Whyte, it's far tougher to roll back those years. Sue's already stopped smoking and lost a lot of weight so can Fiona McDonald and her team of time warriors take care of the rest?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Super-Mom, Super Tired
programme.desc: Three kids in three years, a career, and years of sun worshiping has left this super-mom looking less than super. After hi-tech procedures at the dermatologist, a Pilates session, new outfit and makeup, will this mom look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Taryn Couper
programme.desc: Taryn Couper admits she's stuck in the 1970s so it's up to Fiona McDonald and her team of experts to turn her from Hamilton hippie to boho chic, making her look 10 years younger in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Competitive Edge
programme.desc: As a teen, Luray used to go from the beach to a tanning booth. Now she's after a corporate career, and doesn't want to look like an old lady compared to the other job candidates.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back
programme.desc: In her youth, Catherine was a wild child punk rocker whose bright red mohawk got her elected homecoming queen. But now that Catherine is a single mother of twin teenage daughters, she feels like she's lost her young, eye-catching style.
programme.sub-title: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Make Under
programme.desc: Hair stylist Dawn has a big personality that's hidden her perpetual weight problem. She needs to slim down her appearance. With help, Dawn sheds pounds and years off of her appearance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Most Revealing Reveal Ever
programme.desc: After years of sunbathing, Stefanie hid her sun-damaged skin under frumpy and matronly clothes. But after a flurry of skin treatments, Stefanie stuns her family and friends at one of our most revealing reveals ever!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Old Look Is In Remission
programme.desc: Bobbi's appearance has suffered greatly due to her constant medical treatments and recent mastectomy. After losing her hair and her left breast, she is ready for a change, and has called upon our team of experts to help her through the process.
programme.sub-title: The Old Look Is In Remission

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Trials of Tracy
programme.desc: Tracy is a New York City lawyer who can't find a man. Her frumpy wardrobe and thick glasses keep her home buried in her books for fear of rejection. But our team is on the case to bring this lonely lawyer out of her shell and gain some needed confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA
programme.desc: Natasha has struggled to get her fashion jewelry business off the ground and lost sight of her own looks along the way. She worried that her tired looks and wardrobe of sweats were hurting sales in a business focused on fashion.
programme.sub-title: This Diva is Back and On Track

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Time to Face the Music
programme.desc: Akil is an unemployed music industry executive who feels like his under eye bags, to long dread locks and older looks are getting in the way of getting a new job. 10 Years Younger is on one of it's hardest missions to date!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Tomboy to 10
programme.desc: Stephanie is an avid soccer player, but she doesn't get much of a kick out of life anymore. Stephanie's worst fear about her appearance is her teeth, or rather her missing tooth and she also thinks her skin is aging prematurely.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny has been preparing his pitch for an Endangered Species Project. JLW, a pharmaceutical company, are looking to fund an environmental project and the family hope that this grant money will enable them to buy Leopard's Den and Mara.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Ed release two cheetah brothers together, a symbol of their new partnership, but not all of the family are happy about this new start. Caroline is still furious at what she sees as Danny's betrayal of Du Plessis.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: The family are still estranged following Caroline's decision to move back to the decrepit Clearwater house with Du Plessis. Rosie is determined to reunite everyone, and plans a civilised dinner as a step towards reconciliation.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Danny is in prison, accused of murdering Peeters, but Du Plessis is determined to prove his friend's innocence by any means he can. Du Plessis' first attempt backfires disastrously when he harangues a police officer and ends up in a cell next to Danny.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: With Danny away, and Du Plessis undertaking an ignominious stretch of community service, Ed is left in charge of running the Endangered Species Project.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny and Ed are anxiously preparing for a review with JLW, the pharmaceutical company that fund their Endangered Species Project. They are desperate for it to go smoothly, and as a result are driving the rest of the family mad.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Following the loss of their funding, the family are in dire financial straits. Danny and Ed attempt to get an extension on their mortgage but are refused. Fiona spurs Ed on, telling him that the man she used to know would have a plan for survival.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Strange things are happening at Leopard's Den. The family awake to find frogs everywhere, seemingly having rained down overnight; the giraffe refuses to budge from the front gate and the cheetah is off its food.

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Thomas and Jensen
programme.desc: The doctors meet nine-year-old Thomas who is very rigid in his thought patterns and finds change difficult. Thomas's parents, Nicola and Joe, want to find out what is causing his behaviour and what can be done to help him.

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Bobby and Jessi-Jai
programme.desc: The doctors meet eight-year-old Bobby, who won't eat anything except chocolate, sweets, cakes, chips, cheese, yoghurt and baked beans. Has Bobby got a food phobia and what can his parents do to help him try new healthy foods?

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Charlie and Billy
programme.desc: The doctors meet eight-year-old Charlie who can become so destructive and violent that his mum has had to call the police. After meeting him, Dr Ravi and the experts think that a controversial new diagnosis may be the reason for Charlie's behaviour.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: Thailand is in a state of political unrest and 41-year-old David, a musician from New South Wales, has just been arrested for overstaying his visa. Can the embassy get him out?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: The embassy is called to a young couple in crisis. Their 7 month-old baby girl, Laney, has died from a virus and they need to get her home to Australia. But can they get baby Laney on the plane?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3
programme.desc: The embassy is on high alert after a wealthy Australian banker goes missing. Is he alive? Holed up in a bar somewhere? Or does he not want to be found?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: Jarryd's been busted for drugs in a country where they still have the death penalty. And now he plans to double-cross the Thai authorities and escape to Singapore with his pregnant girlfriend.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: Beau was left for dead by the side of a road after a horrific motorbike crash. Now he wants to discharge himself from hospital. Can the embassy stop him before he self-destructs?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 1
programme.desc: 9 tearaway teens swap hoodies for high heels to battle for a place at a major US teen pageant. First, can beauty queen mentor Michelle Fryatt handle the tears and tantrums when the girls reject a dramatic makeover?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 2
programme.desc: 8 tearaway teenagers hope to become Miss Teen England International. Their next challenge? Championing a good cause. But after a week's swearing and scrapping can the turbulent teens pull off a convincing speech when put to the test?

programme.title: Sports Cars: Lamborghini
programme.desc: The Lamborghini Huracan Spyder snorts through its four tailpipes like a raging bull. It transfers its Italian temperament to the road with all four wheels.

programme.title: Sports Cars: Ferrari
programme.desc: The Ferrari California T is the symbol of luxury and dolce vita. And at the same time, the racing technology in the convertible always drives up the fun factor.

programme.title: Sports Cars: Fiat / Ford / Rimac
programme.desc: The Fiat 124 Spider is one of the most affordable ways to buy a new, zippy convertible, even with the entry-level engine. Technically, the Spider is based on the Mazda MX-5 platform.

programme.title: Sports Cars: McLaren
programme.desc: The McLaren 720S is the official successor to the 650S and follows in pretty big footsteps. We take a closer look at whether it can convince compared to its predecessor.

programme.title: Sports Cars: Mercedes
programme.desc: Poser car or high-performance artist? The Mercedes-AMG C 63 S Cabrio flexes its 510 hp V8 muscles.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Crash Episode 1
programme.desc: When ambition exceeds driving ability and when well-secured racing pros are carried out of the bend, we are there with the camera. Breathtaking stunts by professional drivers and slapsticks by high-powered sheet metal bullets.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Crash Episode 2
programme.desc: When ambition exceeds driving ability and when well-secured racing pros are carried out of the bend, we are there with the camera. Breathtaking stunts by professional drivers and slapsticks by high-powered sheet metal bullets.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Crash Episode 3
programme.desc: When ambition exceeds driving ability and when well-secured racing pros are carried out of the bend, we are there with the camera. Breathtaking stunts by professional drivers and slapsticks by high-powered sheet metal bullets.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Alfa Romeo / Audi
programme.desc: For many people, Alfa Romeo is still the epitome of design, Italian automotive engineering and car racing. The successes of the beautifully designed coupés in the 1960s in particular are still fondly remembered in the Alfa scene.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Amphicar 770 / Bavaria-Tour
programme.desc: The Amphicar 770 is a rare classic car. It may not be the fastest on the road - but it is definitely waterproof.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: BMW
programme.desc: A family van from BMW. The 2 Series GranTourer is big, sporty and chic. But how much BMW sportiness is still in the family vehicle?

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Cadillac / Caterham / Chevrolet
programme.desc: From the outside, you can't tell what kind of power the Cadillac CTS-V has inside. Power that you first have to master.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: DeLorean: a legend on the race track / Uwe Steimle's "Ostalgie" Classics
programme.desc: An idiosyncratic classic and at the same time supporting actor in three cinema films: the DeLorean. Before being used on a race track, the car is put through its paces in the workshop.
